S^2
 S^2=\frac{1}{15-1}\sum_{i=1}^{15} (X_i-\bar X)^2, \text{ where } \bar X=\frac{X_1+\cdots+X_{15}}{15}. 
 \frac{(15-1)S^2}{\sigma^2} \sim \chi^2_{15-1} 
 \Pr(A <\chi^2_{15-1}) = \Pr(\chi^2_{15}<B)= 0.025. 
 \Pr(A<\chi^2_{15}<B) = 0.95. 
 \Pr\left(A<\frac{(15-1)S^2}{\sigma^2}<B\right)=0.95. 
 \Pr\left( \frac{(15-1)S^2}{B} < \sigma^2 < \frac{(15-1)S^2}{A} \right) = 0.95. 
